<blockquote class="wp-block-quote">
<p><strong>Developing national learning materials</strong><br/>Primary school teaching materials on AI and how to use it are currently being developed in the Generation AI project funded by the Strategic Research Council (STN).  <br/><br/><strong>Jari Laru</strong> from the University of Oulu, who has a long experience in teacher training, will be involved in the project as an interaction expert.<br/>- In the future, it will be very important that children and young people are taught AI data literacy and data management skills," says Laru.<br/><br/>The project also aims to develop technology education in primary schools to take better account of the principles of AI.  <br/><br/>- For example, social media applications, Tiktok and others, are based on artificial intelligence. There are different algorithms that profile us, what we are like and [luovat] recommendation systems that present us with content that you still watch this video. Children and young people should be aware of these types of issues," says Laru.  </p>
</blockquote>
